The paper deals with the problem of finding a low discrepancy coloring for sparse set systems, which is a problem in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science. The paper uses techniques from combinatorics, probability theory, and computational geometry. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
